Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.31,0:00:23.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Perfect Crime
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.56,0:00:03.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A perfect crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.60,0:00:08.65,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An unsolvable crime, where nobody can uncover the true circumstances behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.65,0:00:10.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But to put it bluntly,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.40,0:00:15.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a "perfect crime" never amounts to more than a delusional criminal's foolish dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.82,0:00:18.66,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today, let's crack a "perfect crime"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.66,0:00:23.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}as we play back "The Night Baron Murder Case (Case Closed)!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.02,0:00:26.89,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Love lasts forever, riddles are puzzling...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.89,0:00:29.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...and Saturday nights are for mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.40,0:00:31.36,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Night Baron case's conclusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.36,0:00:33.65,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Underneath the mask lies an unexpected killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.65,0:00:35.36,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.36,0:00:37.36,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.36,0:00:39.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.22,0:02:23.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran, the old man, and I went on the Izu Mystery Tour
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.05,0:02:27.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}replacing Dr. Agasa, his friend,\Nand his friend's granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.99,0:02:32.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Whoever determines the organiser's\Nidentity gets to stay for free
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.73,0:02:36.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and receives floppy disks\Ncontaining a certain program.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.27,0:02:42.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But then Ebara{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} -- dressed as\Nthe Night Baron -- fell to his death!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.74,0:02:44.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It was clearly a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.95,0:02:51.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How'd the killer leave after\Npushing Ebara{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} off his veranda?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.41,0:02:55.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He then knocked out a karate\Nexpert guarding the body
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.92,0:02:58.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and appeared before us\Nas the Night Baron!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.71,0:03:00.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran's kicks were useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.42,0:03:02.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could the killer be—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.06,0:03:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that policeman\Nreally a karate expert?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.65,0:03:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a third level black belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.82,0:03:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could've done that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:29.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come to think of it, he did\Ndodge all of Ran's kicks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:33.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the only suspect capable of reading her attacks...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.25,0:03:36.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...was the Japanese karate\Nchampion, Satoru Maeda!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:37.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only he could've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.83,0:03:43.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's why neither of them\Nran after the Night Baron!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.30,0:03:48.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They both realized it was him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:49.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.77,0:03:56.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What would Shin'ichi do in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.23,0:03:58.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What would Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:04:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? If I knew the criminal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.73,0:04:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. For example, what if it was Dr. Agasa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.65,0:04:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd turn him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.44,0:04:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'd flat out say,\N"{\i1}You{\i0} did it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.24,0:04:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you can look cool, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.33,0:04:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.33,0:04:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd probably be dead tired by then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.17,0:04:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd have tried my utmost to prove\Nthat they didn't do it first...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.55,0:04:28.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.84,0:04:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Satoru. If only I hadn't\Nrecommended this tour...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.76,0:04:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay. I came along\Nbecause I wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.23,0:04:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is all the Night Baron's fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.23,0:04:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satoru. Don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.98,0:04:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm off to bed. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.86,0:04:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:53.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Interrogation Room
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:53.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shizuoka Police
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:53.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Authorized Personnel Only
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.04,0:04:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.41,0:04:59.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have a lost item\Nfrom the victim's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.29,0:05:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something odd\Non the security lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.30,0:05:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.09,0:05:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.09,0:05:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is cellophane tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.48,0:05:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.15,0:05:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.02,0:05:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who set the security lock?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.65,0:05:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I locked it from the outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.40,0:05:31.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using this cellophane tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.91,0:05:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you cut yourself\Nan appropriate length
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then fold it in two, leaving a few\Ncentimeters of the sticky part.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you align the lock perpendicularly,\Nplace the tape on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and close the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One tug of the tape and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.51,0:05:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.76,0:05:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pull it more, and... the tape comes\Noff and the evidence disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno... Don't these\Nrooms have auto-locks?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.65,0:06:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can use a room key to see\Nif a room is locked or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.49,0:06:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and you can peel\Nthe tape off if need be!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.53,0:06:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this tip would've been\Nin the killer's blind spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.79,0:06:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah! That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the killer took his key, dressed him up as the Night Baron and threw him over,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.46,0:06:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he left the room and set the\Nsecurity lock using this trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.26,0:06:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after double-checking the lock,\Nhe tossed the key into the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.43,0:06:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would seal the room and\Nmake it look like an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.02,0:06:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you figure out that trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.98,0:06:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw it on a mystery drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.03,0:06:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the issue now is in our six suspects' alibis!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.58,0:06:59.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was\Nwith Ran and Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.29,0:07:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was watching TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kon'no{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was in his\Nroom reading his e-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.17,0:07:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamijō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was in\Nthe pub with Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.30,0:07:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kaneshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Hayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho were in the outside restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.55,0:07:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know Sayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.31,0:07:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she called the\Nfront desk at 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.47,0:07:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, she did ask for a\Nwake-up call at 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.90,0:07:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember her call well. It was\Nright after I heard people screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.86,0:07:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was in Room 2101.\NShe couldn't have done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.28,0:07:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus she was with Ran and Conan\Nwhen they ran into the Night Baron.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.45,0:07:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's in the clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did the killer do that?\NOr even steal the costume?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.75,0:07:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were probably worried when\Nwe realized it was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.17,0:07:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's gotta be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.34,0:07:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have records of\NKon'no{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from Room 2002?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.68,0:08:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He supposedly used the phone for\Nonline access until after 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.77,0:08:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He used it from\N9:45 until 10:06.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't mean\Nhe spoke with anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.44,0:08:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.24,0:08:17.78,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Princess Hotel 2F\NPub Emerald
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.78,0:08:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamjō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drugged my glass!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. You fell asleep afterward...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.20,0:08:28.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Knew it! Kamijō{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s pills {\i1}were{\i0} a sleeping drug!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.71,0:08:31.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did she drug the old man to create an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.42,0:08:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.38,0:08:38.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to the restroom,\Nbut returned five minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.39,0:08:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she was here when\Nthe murder occurred?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.01,0:08:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. She left when she\Nheard the commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.64,0:08:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were those old folks really here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.56,0:08:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. They rushed to the front of\Nthe crowd after hearing someone fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.28,0:08:58.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The front?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.32,0:09:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap! I suspected them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay. We've narrowed\Nit down to two suspects now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.58,0:09:07.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.21,0:09:10.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The only ones with unconfirmed alibis
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.96,0:09:13.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}are Kon'no{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and Maeda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.80,0:09:17.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maeda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was with us in\Nthe observation lounge,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.17,0:09:21.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but he's the one who checked\Nthe time, so he could've lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:27.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And considering that the knocked-out\Nofficer was a karate expert,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.35,0:09:31.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maeda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} must be the one who...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.78,0:09:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.44,0:09:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.78,0:09:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found an alibi for Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.87,0:09:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he left us, he met some\Nfans of his at the lounge entrance!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.50,0:09:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They even asked for the date\Nand time with his autographs!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.96,0:09:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time was 10:03!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.21,0:09:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're sure of it, because they\Neven checked their own watches!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.97,0:10:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you bring them here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.93,0:10:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! I'll go get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.89,0:10:09.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ah! So Maeda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} wasn't the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.93,0:10:10.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:14.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then why didn't he mention\Nit when he was questioned?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.73,0:10:16.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's an airtight alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:19.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe he couldn't mention it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.15,0:10:20.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:26.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's the pen I dropped.\NIt's leaking ink from the shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:30.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10be6}Not surprising... it {\i1}did{\i0} fall from\NEbara{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s room on the 21st floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:31.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.25,0:10:37.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's odd. He fell off the\Nsame veranda but hit the statue...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.09,0:10:40.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, right. The wind blew it over...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.01,0:10:41.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The wind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.97,0:10:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, miss waitress!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.18,0:10:45.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.18,0:10:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the wind blowing\Nwhen that person fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,\Nthere was a strong wind...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.10,0:10:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It constantly blows at\Nnight this time of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:58.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the left of that\Nstatue to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:11:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's our famous "Princess Wind!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.32,0:11:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a lot stronger higher up, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:05.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:08.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's one place where the wind...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:16.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't believe I didn't realize something this simple...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.33,0:11:19.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I'm sure! That's the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! The knocked-out\Nofficer was a karate expert?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.30,0:11:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! Now I know who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.84,0:11:31.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will now begin my explanation!\NGather all the suspects here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.39,0:11:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.73,0:11:33.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.44,0:11:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The detective wants you to do\Nthis stuff in the suspects' rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.53,0:11:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.24,0:11:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He says it's an experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that it'll prove who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.54,0:11:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for your alibis for\Nwhen the victim fell at 10:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.17,0:12:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The alibis of Kaneshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\NHayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Sayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Kamijō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.05,0:12:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,have all been confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.63,0:12:09.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn it! Where's the signal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones with vague alibis
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.10,0:12:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,are Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was in\Nthe observation lounge,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.44,0:12:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Kon'no{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.40,0:12:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but after murdering the victim,\Nthe killer stupidly stole the costume
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.65,0:12:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from the office where the body was
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.32,0:12:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then ran into\NSayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.16,0:12:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...unaware that the officer he\Nknocked out was a karate expert!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.75,0:12:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A karate expert?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.25,0:12:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.21,0:12:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one capable of knocking\Nsuch a person out in one blow...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.50,0:12:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is the former Japanese karate\Nchampion, Satoru Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.13,0:12:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.47,0:12:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s not the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.31,0:12:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was with {\i1}them{\i0} during the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.52,0:12:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.77,0:12:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.44,0:13:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.07,0:13:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you get serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:06.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer is the\Nalibi-less Shirō Kon'no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be fooled by\Nhis looks, people!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.83,0:13:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hide it as he may, this man\Nis actually a karate expert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.71,0:13:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.42,0:13:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quit fooling around!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.25,0:13:27.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's the signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.72,0:13:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.89,0:13:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, the killer's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.39,0:13:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:41.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, enough of this foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.44,0:13:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on. This is Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s deduction pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.28,0:13:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.03,0:13:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I begin my deduction, please step away from the statue and out of harm's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.12,0:14:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.87,0:14:02.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are these?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.47,0:14:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blankets that I had dressed up\Nas people and dropped from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dropped from each of the suspects'\Nrooms, with their numbers on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Room 2101!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.23,0:14:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is from Tokio Ebara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room,\Nwhere the murder occurred!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.90,0:14:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he fell directly\Nonto that statue!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.78,0:14:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't have been carried\Nthis far by the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.99,0:14:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was. By the "Princess Wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.91,0:14:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This strong wind blows past\Nthe hotel at nights this time of year...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.59,0:14:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the left of the statue to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kaneshiro, Hayashi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ebara
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kamijō
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kon'no
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Maeda, Sayama
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Princess Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:50.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,Statue
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.88,0:14:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was also blowing when the\Nvictim fell. Correct, Ms. Waitress?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.85,0:15:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! I think it was blowing\Neven harder than it is now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.31,0:15:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, he was wearing a Night Baron outfit with high air resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.27,0:15:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had been pushed\Noff his own veranda,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.44,0:15:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt he would've fallen\Nonto the statue directly below.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the blanket dropped from\NKaneshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room one floor below
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.20,0:15:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is lying far off to the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.25,0:15:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.46,0:15:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were fooled by the glove on\Nthe veranda and the locked room trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.75,0:15:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those weren't meant to simply\Nmake it look like an accident—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.26,0:15:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they were also traps to make it\Nlook like that's where it happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.26,0:15:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct. The killer didn't\Nlock the room after the murder;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.27,0:15:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he locked it before committing\Nthe murder in his own room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.94,0:15:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning the most suspect are...\Nthe blankets lying by the statue!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.15,0:15:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Room 2102's Kamijō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\NRoom 2002's Kon'no{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.33,0:16:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Room 1901's Sayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.25,0:16:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a coincidence! After all,\Neveryone else's are by the statue, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.13,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's indeed a coincidence\Nthat it was pierced,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's no coincidence\Nthat it fell there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, the killer is neither\NKamijō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} nor Kon'no{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.98,0:16:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their windows are off to\Nthe side of the victim's veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.02,0:16:35.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at the point of impact,\Nit would be instantly obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.28,0:16:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that he didn't fall from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.91,0:16:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Sayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room is\Ndirectly below theirs!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her room's blanket must've landed there by coincidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.70,0:16:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.37,0:16:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.67,0:16:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One directly below the victim's\Nveranda where there's almost no wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.59,0:17:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The call she made to the\Nfront desk to create an alibi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.18,0:17:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,conversely proves that she was in\Nthe room at the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.60,0:17:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then the killer's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.69,0:17:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! I did it! I pushed him off!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.48,0:17:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akiko didn't do it!\NShe even ran into the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.45,0:17:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...me, dressed as the Night Baron!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.32,0:17:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was me!\NI did it all alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.41,0:17:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.45,0:17:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it {\i1}was{\i0} you who did\Nthat to cover for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.33,0:17:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cover for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.58,0:17:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.58,0:17:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stole the Night Baron\Ncostume and ran into her
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to rid her of all suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.76,0:17:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he was not an accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.22,0:17:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did it of his own accord when\Nhe realized who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Upon seeing the\Nnecktie's knot, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.15,0:17:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unclear if that was the\Nkiller's own style or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.90,0:17:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did find\Nsomething in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.15,0:18:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something that was floating\Nin the pool later...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.99,0:18:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wig!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.62,0:18:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.99,0:18:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was likely convinced when he\Nfound it among the killer's things...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.37,0:18:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Convinced that she was the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.83,0:18:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.29,0:18:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wig was in the room because\NEbara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the Night Baron
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.30,0:18:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,happened to have the same hairstyle,\Nmaking it unnecessary!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.26,0:18:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}that's{\i0} why he risked\Nrunning into her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.09,0:18:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with the stolen costume\Nand the wig on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.14,0:18:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. And he was prepared to be caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.06,0:18:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he kept quiet about\Nhaving people to vouch for his alibi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was because it would cause\Nproblems if he were caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He planned to take the fall in place\Nof Akiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} if it came down to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.49,0:18:50.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, my perfect\Ncrime was ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.00,0:18:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, I did it!\NI killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.88,0:18:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To avenge my brother who he\Nkilled three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Killed!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.97,0:19:04.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pretty much!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.09,0:19:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hacked the "Workshop" software\Nmy brother bet the company on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Workshop?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.48,0:19:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's the software Ebara\Nsold me three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had I known it was stolen,\NI would've taken it off the market!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.90,0:19:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother jumped off the\Ncompany building before that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.07,0:19:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've lived to avenge\Nhim ever since...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.24,0:19:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and then I came up\Nwith this Mystery Tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My lure was the infamous\N"Night Baron" virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.00,0:19:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He immediately took the bait...\Nunaware that it didn't exist...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. After I drove Satoru off,\Nthe bait I used to lure Ebara
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.05,0:19:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,into our room was\Nonce again the virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.14,0:19:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He rushed over immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.60,0:19:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,once he got a whiff of\Nthe virus's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.02,0:20:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I put sleeping pills in his\Ndrink, locked his room as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.28,0:20:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then sent him plummeting from my room!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.40,0:20:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.78,0:20:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My only oversight was that you,\NKogoro Mouri, would be on the tour!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you didn't even blink after\NI pushed Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} into the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.00,0:20:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satoru. This is the kind of woman I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.84,0:20:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So forget about me already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.64,0:20:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.35,0:20:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting until you get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.27,0:20:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You moron...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.11,0:20:51.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After that, Akiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} slightly nodded and got into the police car.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.07,0:20:56.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maeda{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was taken into another\Ncar for police obstruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.54,0:21:01.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but Detective Yokomizo says he may get off on mitigating circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.50,0:21:05.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As we watched the cars leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.26,0:21:10.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the Princess Wind\Ncried sadly around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.36,0:22:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? So {\i1}that's{\i0} why you drugged his drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.30,0:22:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.13,0:22:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured I could check the Great Detective's notes to find out who the Night Baron was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.81,0:22:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But his notebook was blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.04,0:22:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would you go that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.61,0:22:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only wanted the virus so\NI could make a vaccine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.15,0:22:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like they wanted\Nit for bad reasons, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.53,0:22:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.74,0:23:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I simply wished to punish\Nthe owner of the virus
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.12,0:23:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that ruined my beloved\Nsoftware "son" four years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.71,0:23:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you even faked your bad eyesight?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.73,0:23:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.05,0:23:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had hoped to keep people off guard...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.68,0:23:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of software was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.60,0:23:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.39,0:23:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Project: High Schoolgirl Paradise," sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.35,0:23:28.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.71,0:23:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! I heard\Nyou scoured the entire hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.78,0:23:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to prove Maeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.11,0:23:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really looked up to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.53,0:23:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus {\i1}he{\i0} taught me that you can't ever give up until the very end...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.66,0:23:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.04,0:23:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You called your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.57,0:23:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's no it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.59,0:23:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's this "he?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.31,0:23:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not you too, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.55,0:23:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know who I mean! That wandering mystery geek!
